            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">36.601-3</ph> Applicable contracting procedures.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d2327e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2341e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
					          </p>
					          <ol id="d2327e23" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2341e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                For facility design contracts, the statement of work shall require that the architect-engineer specify, in the construction design specifications, use of the maximum practicable amount of recovered materials consistent with the performance requirements, availability, price reasonableness, and cost-effectiveness. Where appropriate, the statement of work also shall require the architect-engineer to consider energy conservation, pollution prevention, and waste reduction to the maximum extent practicable in developing the construction design specifications.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2341e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Facility design solicitations and contracts that include the specification of energy-consuming products must comply with the requirements at <xref href="FAR-i1094859.dita#i1094859"
                              base="i1094859"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  23.2</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2341e50" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Sources for contracts for architect-engineer services shall be selected in accordance with the procedures in this subpart rather than the solicitation or source selection procedures prescribed in <xref href="FAR-i1112458.dita#i1112458"
                        base="i1112458"
                        outputclass="fm:Parts"
                        class="- topic/xref ">parts  13</xref>, <xref href="FAR-i1111055.dita#i1111055"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">14</xref>, and <xref href="FAR-i1109360.dita#i1109360"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15</xref> of this regulation.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2341e68" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            When the contract statement of work includes both architect-engineer services and other services, the contracting officer shall follow the procedures in this subpart if the statement of work, substantially or to a dominant extent, specifies performance or approval by a registered or licensed architect or engineer. If the statement of work does not specify such performance or approval, the contracting officer shall follow the procedures in <xref href="FAR-i1112458.dita#i1112458"
                        base="i1112458"
                        outputclass="fm:Parts"
                        class="- topic/xref ">parts  13</xref>, <xref href="FAR-i1111055.dita#i1111055"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">14</xref>, or <xref href="FAR-i1109360.dita#i1109360"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2341e86" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Other than “incidental services” as specified in the definition of architect-engineer services in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref> and in <xref href="FAR-i1078339.dita#i1078339"
                        base="i1078339"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">36.601-4</xref>(a)(3), services that do not require performance by a registered or licensed architect or engineer, notwithstanding the fact that architect-engineers also may perform those services, should be acquired pursuant to <xref href="FAR-i1112458.dita#i1112458"
                        base="i1112458"
                        outputclass="fm:Parts"
                        class="- topic/xref ">parts  13</xref>, <xref href="FAR-i1111055.dita#i1111055"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">14</xref>, and <xref href="FAR-i1109360.dita#i1109360"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15</xref>.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
